A 28-year-old cook was found dead in the mall of San Francisco
The 28-year-old chef, who recently moved to San Francisco, was found dead in the stairwell of a local shopping center this week.
However, the victim's brother says that he can not imagine someone who would like to hurt him, noting: "At last things were going well with him."
"The body, found at Westfield Mall on Wednesday morning, was identified as 28-year-old San Francisco resident Frank Galicia," the San Francisco Forensic Bureau said.
The San Francisco Police Department reports that death was classified as murder and the investigation continues.
The victim's brother, Luis Galicia, told the KGO channel of the ABC television station in San Francisco that Frank, the past cook of the distribution line in Boston, got his dream job as a chef at the San Francisco's Sons & Daughters restaurant six months ago.
A spokesman for Sons & Daughters said that they were "shocked and depressed" by his death.
"We are a small team that works as a friendly family and it will be very missed," the representative said.
Our thoughts and condolences to Frank's family and friends in this difficult period.
Luis Galicia said that Frank first stayed at the hostels, but recently "At last things were going well with him."
"He found an apartment, he met a girl," - Luis Galicia told KGO.
Luis Galicia said he can not imagine someone who would like to hurt his younger brother.
He had a good heart and a big heart.
His way of communication with the family has always been to prepare us some dish, cook dinner for us, "said Luis Galicia.
He never wanted to be involved in any quarrel.
He was a brother who sailed with the flow.
"With all the bad things happening to this world, it was that uncut diamond that shone brightly every day," he said.
All those who own the information are asked to call the SFPD Hotline at 415-575-4444.
