The size of the national debt of Italy increased to record figures
The size of the national debt of Italy in June 2016 exceeded 2,248 trillion euros.
The central bank said that this amount is the historical maximum, RIA Novosti reported.
The previous negative record was set in May this year.
Then the size of the national debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that for the first half of the debt load of Italy increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, Italy's public debt was 132.7% of the country's GDP.
Meanwhile, the Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pierre Carlo Padoan forecasted a decline in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 - to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in Domodedovo.
141 people received charity payments from the Aviation Fund, which was created by the management of the Domodedovo airport to help those affected by the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reported.
According to Alexander Vlasov, airport spokesman, two more applications are under consideration.
"On the part of the fund, charity payments are continuing to those who suffered from the terrorist act of 2011 and are provided with comprehensive assistance in resolving existing issues," Vlasov added, recalling that specifically to facilitate interaction with victims, a fund website was created containing full information on the procedure for providing charitable assistance.
In 2011, the suicide bomber launched an explosive device in the Domodedovo airport.
As a result of the terrorist attack, 37 people were killed and 172 more were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years
An international group of biologists came to the conclusion that the longest living vertebrate is the Greenland polar shark, which can live about 500 years, reports RT.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, whose length exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years.
Biologists believe that an important role in the longevity of the shark is played by low metabolism, which leads to a slow development.
The females of Greenland sharks reach puberty only by 150 years.
Earlier it was believed that the "neighbor" of the shark-the Greenland whale-lived the longest of vertebrates.
The oldest specimen, known to scientists, was slightly over 210 years old.
