Prolong fruiting.
What can I do to make the harvest till the end of the season?
Yulia Belopukhova, agronomist and dacha woman tells.
Tall tomatoes are time to arrange a haircut: remove new stepsons, cut off the tops, remove all leaves to the penultimate brush with fruits and inflorescences with small ovaries - they will not have time to ripen.
All tomatoes, irrespective of the "constitution", as well as peppers and eggplants, are fed with an ash-superphosphate extract, processed with biological preparations (Morozov - for accelerating the filling and growth of fruits, Phytosporin-M, Phytolavin, Gamair, Bactofit for diseases, Immunocytophyte for immunity, Bitoxibacillin, Lepidocide, Phyto-vermis - if there are pests).
Of the chemicals in late summer is to use only copper sulfate, colloidal sulfur and green soap.
We make the last watering of plants.
Long-flowered cucumbers in the greenhouse are lowered from the trellis so that the lower, bare part of the stem (25-40 cm) lies on the ground, watered with warm water and Zircon solution, pour the stem with 5-7 cm of compost.
Extend the fruiting zucchini is also easy: cut old leaves, pour with warm water and a solution of complex fertilizer, sprinkle fertile soil under the bush.
To protect against nighttime colds, place an arc over the garden with cover material.
Keep plants open during the day and close them after sunset.
Signs of the end.
What does it mean that Russia is emerging from the crisis?
Economists saw signs of Russia's withdrawal from the longest recession in the last twenty years.
As analysts interviewed by Bloomberg analysts, Russia's GDP demonstrates a positive trend - in the second quarter, GDP fell by 0.8% in annual terms.
This indicator is minimal since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data of Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development recently announced stabilization of the situation.
Ahead - slow growth.
According to CBR experts, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
"The index estimate of Russia's GDP suggests that the recession has been left behind, and ahead is a slow growth of the economy," the Bank of Russia bulletin says What Trends Say.
Modular estimation of GDP for the current quarter increased the regulatory specialists to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter was 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter the decline in the Russian GDP stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally adjusted decline in GDP was 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter the decline stopped: in April it was 0.2%, and in May and June the GDP change was in the range of 0-0.15 ", - quotes the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development of the RIA Novosti.
The slowdown in the rate of decline of the Russian economy during the last five quarters indicates that the "bottom is over".
Among other markers, indicating signs of revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth of demand for electricity and rail transportation, business revival.
If we make an amendment to the fact that the year is a leap year, it is clear that the dynamics in plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this the lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight traffic, but it is difficult to obtain accurate data, and plus or minus 0.5% of the semi-annual volume can also be explained by seasonality, "explains Kirill Yakovenko from ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilizing the Russian economy.
For example, reducing the price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, the last two weeks Rosstat fixes deflation.
Prices in Russia declined for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble, which, although it showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, increased by 12% in August from the beginning of the year.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy, "Yakovenko said.
In addition, since April in Russia there has been an increase in industrial production.
In June, the indicator grew by 1.7%.
Slowing down the foreign trade turnover slows down from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
Positive dynamics is also demonstrated by the situation on the labor market, where the unemployment rate fell to 5.4%.
Below it was only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the favorable situation in the labor market, the question of the real disposable income of the population leaves much to be desired.
In annual terms, the indicator is reduced by 4.8%.
This factor can hamper economic recovery, as household expenditures make a significant contribution to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy, their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, the rigid policy of the Bank of Russia can also be cited as a risk factor for economic growth.
The regulator holds the rate at 10.5%, which is not the best way to affect the real sector.
A negative factor is the insufficiently high level of investment, which hampers the development of industrial potential.
But in general, we can assume that by the end of the year the rate of decline in the Russian economy will slow to -0.5% from -3.7% in 2015, "says Irina Rogova, an analyst at the Forex Club.
The process of naturalization of athletes, recently launched in Russian football and well established in winter sports at the Sochi Olympics, is not yet actively developed in summer sports.
If in the Olympic Games in Rio for Russia and act former foreigners, in most cases it is about the natives of countries - the former Soviet republics.
But in Rio de Janeiro, we can observe the reverse process - a fairly large number of Russians act under the flags of other states.
In each case, the history of the change of citizenship is different.
Someone's parents were taken to another country as a child, leaving no choice.
Someone could not stand the competition for a place in the Russian team.
And some people thought that better conditions for development in sport would be created abroad.
"AIF.ru" found at least 16 athletes who decided to change their Russian citizenship.
In the German passport of the 27-year-old girl it is written that her name is Lisa Ryzhikh.
But earlier it was, of course, Elizabeth.
She was born in 1988 in the city of Omsk.
In just four years, as soon as the Soviet Union collapsed, Lisa's parents decided to emigrate to Germany.
The girl had no choice.
There she decided to follow in the footsteps of her older sister - to do athletics.
Like her sister, Lisa chose pole vaulting.
Staying in Russia, she could hardly "move the throne" Elena Isinbayeva.
Unfortunately, at the Olympics in Rio, Lisa will be our only fellow countryman, albeit a former, in the sector for pole vaulting.
Her best achievements in this sport are the bronze of the 2010 European Championship and the silver of the continental championship in 2016, which she won again in the absence of Elena Isinbayeva.
29-year-old Elena Pirozhkova was born in Novokuznetsk in 1986.
Her parents are religious propagandists of the evangelical direction.
In many ways, because of their faith, they left for the US when the girl was only three years old.
In addition to Helen, the family grew eight more children.
They all lived in a small town in Greenfield, Massachusetts.
Lena began to get involved in wrestling in school.
Featuring good results, she moved to the city of Colorado Springs, where the US Training Center continued her studies under the leadership of another former Russian Vladislav Izboynikov.
At the 2012 London Olympics, Elena lost in her first fight.
But at the World Championships in the same year - a victory.
Before that, by the way, she managed to win silver at the 2010 World Championship.
After that, there were bronze in 2013 and silver in 2014.
26-year-old Maria was born in the city of Yaroslavl, where for the first time she got acquainted with synchronized swimming.
But to say that she was brought up by our coaches in Russia would be wrong.
Soon, the girl's family decided to emigrate to the US and settle in the city of Colorado.
There Maria continued her studies.
Soon she was already a member of the US team and showed excellent results in the Pan-American Games.
It is clear that at a serious international level it can not compete with Russian synchronists, but for America its performance is a ceiling.
A new name that sounds strange in Russian, Christina Shaldybina received at 11 when her parents decided to continue teaching the girl to rhythmic gymnastics overseas.
Up to this point, the girl was engaged in a favorite sport in her native Yaroslavl.
Having emigrated to the USA, she quickly joined the junior national team of this country, and later broke into the main national team.
At the Pan-American Games, 19-year-old Kristen won gold and silver.
For the first positions on the world stage, of course, she did not have to fight, but for the USA she organized a real breakthrough - she brought the star-striped team to the Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro.
Another of our former "artist" is Yana Berezko-Marggrander, who is in favor of the German national team.
Yana was born in Togliatti.
In 2008, when the girl was 13 years old, the family decided to move to Germany - where the girl had more prospects to get into the national team.
Soon she already represented her country at the 2012 London Olympics.
There, however, Yana was able to take only 17 place, not enough to get into the final competitions in the personal championship.
But two years before that, she managed to win the bronze medal of the Olympic Games - juniors.
Another gymnast, only this time sports - Irina Sazonova.
If the ways of emigration of the above-mentioned athletes can be called standard, the choice of Irina's family is very unusual - Iceland.
Ira is a pupil of the Volgograd sports school.
Naturally, in Iceland she immediately became the champion of the country.
True, Irina is still training in Russia - she specially comes to her homeland not to lose her skill.
In Rio, she did not perform as well as she would like.
The best place is 40 in personal all-around.
Information about the swimmer Maria Ugolkova in the Russian information space is extremely small.
For a very long time, Maria lives and trains in Switzerland.
However, for a long time she acted under the Russian flag, showing good results - there was even a country record at a distance of 200 meters butterfly.
In 2015 she received Swiss citizenship and began to perform under the red-and-white flag.
In Rio, her best performance is the 14th place in the 4 × 100 relay race.
To get into the games, the girl launched a crowdaming project, thanks to which she was able to collect about 6,000 francs, which allowed her to pay for the preparation for the Olympics.
