During this time the native of Khasavyurt managed to become a three-time winner of the European Championships, the champion of Russia, the master of sports of Russia of international class.
When he stopped getting into our national team, it's time to think about changing citizenship.
For several years, the talented wrestler disappeared from sports platforms.
The triumphant return took place at the Asian championship in 2016 - Batirov already represented Bahrain, for which he won a gold medal and got a ticket to the Olympics in Rio.
About another ex-Russian, Mikhail Kudinov, in his homeland is known even less than even about the Swiss swimmer Maria Ugolkov.
The fact is that his parents emigrated from Vladivostok to New Zealand, when the boy was very young.
It was there that Mikhail began to practice gymnastics.
He did not achieve great success at the international level.
In Rio, his best result was the 40th place in the qualification on parallel bars.
But for New Zealand, even getting into the Olympic Games in gymnastics is a breakthrough.
When Nastya, born in Moscow in 1985, was only 9 years old, her family emigrated to Israel.
There, the girl continued her synchronized swimming classes, showing high results at the national level.
In 2014, at the European Championships in Berlin, the girl took the 6th place in synchronized swimming.
In the duet with Eugene Tetelbaum, Anastasia took eighth place.
In the solo program she was fifth.
Like Anastasia, 23-year-old Dmitri Kreutter speaks for the Israeli national team.
When the boy was only 6 years old, his mother decided to repatriate to Israel.
In 2009, at 17, Dmitri has already become the champion of the country.
In the same year he won the Youth World Championship.
A year later, Kreuter wins the gold of the youth Olympic Games in Singapore.
In addition to jumps in height, Dmitry is engaged in long jump and triple jump.
31-year-old Albert - another native of Khasavyurt, who after long speeches for Russia decided to change his sports citizenship.
However, unlike Batirov, Albert chose Romania, which he will represent in Rio.
In Russia, he was in favor of the School of Higher Sports Skill of Krasnoyarsk, in 2011 even becoming the champion of the country.
28-year-old Oleg Antonov was born in Moscow in the family of the USSR national volleyball player Yaroslav Antonov.
Just a year before the birth of his son Yaroslav was recognized as the best volleyball player of the planet.
Soon he decided to continue his career in Italy.
In the same place, the family stayed on permanent residence.
In 2015, as part of the national team, he became a bronze medalist at the European Championships held on the territory of his new homeland.
Hajiyev was born in Chechnya in 1994 and was with his family in the midst of the war.
Ten years later, the parents decided to emigrate.
The original goal was Norway, but it was not possible to get to this northern country - it was necessary to go to France, to Nice.
There Zelimkhan continued to study free-style wrestling.
Soon he won the world championship among juniors, and later qualified for participation in the Olympic Games.
In Rio, he will be the only representative of France in the wrestling tournament.
And again a free fight, and again a former Russian.
This time we will talk about a native of North Ossetia, who emigrated to Spain - about Taymuraz Friyev.
At the end of December 2012, he was granted Spanish citizenship, and currently he is in favor of the national team of this country.
Before that, however, the 30-year-old athlete managed to celebrate high results in Russia.
He became the bronze medalist of the national championships in 2007 and 2008.
Tired of failures in the team, Taimuraz decided to change sports citizenship.
The last in our list is a Chechen boxer, born in 1995 in the capital of Dagestan, Makhachkala, - Artur Biyarslanov.
When the boy was ten years old, the parents took the family across Azerbaijan to Canada.
There Arthur, on the advice of his older brother, began boxing.
Since then, Arthur has become the champion of Canada three times, and in 2012 he became the world champion among the youth.
In 2015, Biyarslanov won the gold of the Pan-American Games, the first for his new homeland since 1975.
The head of the presidential administration Anton Vaino.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Vaino head of the Russian presidential administration.
Earlier this post was occupied by Sergey Ivanov.
"The head of state, through his decree, appointed Anton Vaino as the head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation, releasing him from his post," the decree signed by Putin and published on the Kremlin website says.
Since May 2012, Vaino was deputy head of the presidential administration.
Anton Eduardovich Vaino was born on February 17, 1972 in Tallinn.
Father - Eduard Vaino, Chairman of the Business Council of Cuba-Russia in the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice-President for External Relations and Cooperation with Shareholders of AvtoVAZ.
Grandfather - Karl Vaino - from1978 to 1988 the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001 he worked in the Russian Embassy in Japan, then in the Second Asia Department of the Russian Foreign Ministry.
From 2002 to 2004, he held various positions in the Office of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 he was deputy head of the Protocol and Organizational Department of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007 - First Deputy Head of Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008 - Deputy Head of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On April 25, 2008 he was appointed the head of the protocol of the Chairman of the Government of the Russian Federation, Deputy Head of the Staff of the Government of the Russian Federation.
Since December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Government Office of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012 he was appointed deputy head of the presidential administration.
Fluent in English and Japanese.
Actual state adviser of the Russian Federation of 1 class (class rank awarded by the Presidential Decree of January 22, 2008)
Honorary Diploma of the President of the Russian Federation (February 16, 2012) for his services in supporting the activities of the government of the Russian Federation and for many years of conscientious work.
Gratitude from the President of the Russian Federation (November 24, 2005) for his services in the preparation and holding of ceremonial events dedicated to the 60th anniversary of the Victory in the Great Patriotic War.
He is married and has a son.
