Moscow's Gazstroibank remained without a license from the Central Bank.
On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia revoked the license for banking operations from the credit institution Joint-Stock Commercial Bank "Gazstroybank", registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC JSCB "GAZSTROYBANK" conducted a highly risky credit policy related to the placement of cash in low-quality assets.
An adequate assessment of the risks accepted at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets led to the appearance of the credit organization's grounds for implementing measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in conducting doubtful transit operations.
A temporary administration is appointed in the bank until the time of appointment to the bankruptcy commissioner or liquidator.
Powers of executive bodies of the credit organization in accordance with federal laws are suspended.
Joint-stock company AKB "GAZSTROYBANK" - the participant of system of insurance of contributions.
Recall that the payment of insurance compensation to depositors of the bank, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with the Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On insurance of individuals' deposits in the banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% of the balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles in aggregate per one depositor.
Payments, according to the Agency for Deposit Insurance, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
According to the financial statements, as of August 1, 2016, JSCB "GAZSTROYBANK" held 335th place in the banking system of the Russian Federation.
