In particular, the ban included meat and meat products, fish, seafood, vegetables, fruits and dairy products.
The utilization of foodstuffs imported into the country bypassing the embargo is being carried out in Russia since August 2015.
Only for the first quarter of 2016 about 100 tons of banned products were seized from the sale.
