The Spiritual Administration of Muslims (DUM) of Tatarstan refuses to use the Russian language in mosques.
Yesterday the plenum of the DUM ordered its imams to conduct Friday sermons only in Tatar, in order to compel young Tatars to "study their native language."
The administration states that this "in no case infringes" the rights of Muslims of other nationalities.
Some mosques in Kazan complain that the Tatar language is not understood by up to 60% of the parishioners, among them foreign students, migrants and Tatars themselves.
The Imams fear that their preaching in the Tatar "will not reach the whole audience."
Yesterday, the Plenum of the DUM of Tatarstan unanimously decided to hold Friday sermons in the mosques of the republic only in the Tatar language.
As Mufti of Tatarstan Kamil Samigullin said, this should be an incentive for young Tatars "to learn their native language."
"For those who say that it is" hard ", in every big mosque we intend to organize lessons of the Tatar language absolutely free of charge," Mr. Samigullin promised.
He added that "the decision has already entered into force" and today in all mosques the sermons "must already be in the Tatar language".
He recalled that the DUM of Tatarstan publishes the magazine "Shura" with typical sermons in the Tatar language.
The Imam, who does not speak Tatar well enough, "can thoroughly prepare for them".
The DUM of Tatarstan unites more than a thousand parishes in all municipalities of the republic.
According to the mufti, in the districts Friday sermons are conducted exclusively in the Tatar language.
At the same time in Kazan, a number of mosques used to be predominantly Russian.
In particular, as pointed out by the mufti, it was practiced in the Barnaul mosque, Zakabannaya and "Eniler".
However, Mr. Mukhametshin stressed, the leadership sets the task that all students should possess both state languages of the republic, regardless of nationality.
"There can be no question of any infringement of non-Muslim Muslims," Mr. Mukhametshin stressed, explaining that the sermon "is not an obligatory, the main part of prayer."
At the same time, Namaz will continue to be read in Arabic, lectures and lessons will be kept in mosques in Russian.
At the same time, Rafik Mukhametshin told Kommersant that there was no serious threat of expelling the Tatar language from the mosques.
In addition to Russian and Tatar, other languages, for example, Uzbek or Tajik, according to his information, are not used in sermons in the republic.
The decision of the Duma was actively supported by the Executive Committee of the World Congress of Tatars (CGT).
The head of the VKT executive committee, Rinat Zakirov, told Kommersant: "Mosques are an important part of our national life."
It would be sad if the Tatar language had left this sphere.
He noted that the conduct of sermons only in the Tatar language "the desire of the imams themselves," but in the executive committee of the CGT "consider this right."
The Imams interviewed by Kommersant who conducted the sermons in Russian are ready to execute the decision of the DUM, but they believe that the parishioners will have difficulty understanding clergymen.
Tatars and Russians go to the mosque.
Many do not understand the language.
They, of course, will be tugovato.
"We will have to rebuild," says Farahat Mavleddinov, imam of the Burnaev Mosque.
According to him, sermons in Russian are closer even to many Tatars, since "Russian and in schools, and in kindergartens, on radio - everywhere from the beginning."
However, he believes that the mosque will be able to continue the lessons and lectures in Russian, which are held on other days.
We rely on Allah.
Allah will show a way out of this situation, "he concluded.
But about 60% of us do not know the Tatar language.
They are Uzbeks, Tajiks, and Azerbaijanis.
Many foreign students come to us: Africans, Arabs.
"That's why we switched to Russian for four years," the imam said.
He believes that in the Tatar language, sermons will "reach a narrower range and will not reach the entire audience."
But we will obey the decision of the plenum.
Just the result of the sermons will be different.
But time will tell.
"For me, for example, it will only be easier, because the Tatar language is my native language," concluded Gabdulla Galiullin.
The former director of the FSIN was put on trial
The Moscow prosecutor's office approved the indictment on the criminal investigation into the criminal investigation into the budget of the Federal Penitentiary Service (FSIN) of Russia.
Before the trial, ex-head of the prison department Alexander Reymer and his deputy, who caused FSIN damages worth more than 2.7 billion rubles.
The capital prosecutor's office sent a criminal case against the former director of the FSIN of Russia, Alexander Reimer, his former deputy Nikolay Krivolapov, and the director of the FSUE "Information and Technical Support and Communication Center of the Federal Service for the Execution of Punishments" (FSUE CITOS), Viktor Defendinov, to the Zamoskvoretsky District Court.
Depending on the role and degree of participation in the commission of crimes, they are accused by the GSS of the Russian Federation for the violation of Article 3 of Article 285 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (abuse of official powers resulting in grave consequences), Part 4, Article 159 of the Criminal Code (fraud committed using his official position as part of an organized group, on a large scale).
In addition, Krivolapov is charged under part 1 of Article 222 of the Criminal Code (illegal acquisition and storage of ammunition).
According to the version of the TFR, in 2010-2012 these individuals fraudulently abducted from the state treasury budget funds allocated by the Federal Penitentiary Service to provide the system with electronic monitoring systems of controlled entities, the so-called electronic bracelets.
In order to steal budget money, the group members developed a scheme according to which the company controlled by it, FGUP CITOS, with which the relevant state contracts were concluded, manufactured technical control and surveillance equipment, including electronic bracelets, and sold at prices that were inflated several times.
Despite the fact that FGUP CITOS did not have production equipment, buildings, facilities for locating production facilities that allow creating a complete cycle of production of electronic bracelets, five state contracts worth more than 3.3 billion rubles were signed between him and the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia.
As a result of this scheme, more than 2 billion rubles were on the accounts of the FSUE Samara branch, of which 1.2 billion rubles was stolen.
According to the investigation, more than 140 million rubles of cash money was personally received by Mr. Reimer in his office from one of the accomplices, a criminal case against which was allocated to a separate proceeding.
Nikolai Krivolapov, who participated in the machinations, found unknown sources of ammunition for the award pistol, which allowed him to show additional charges.
In this case, the volume of which was 133 volumes, the FSIN to the defendants filed an action for compensation of material damage in the amount of 2.7 billion rubles.
Footballer Hakan Shukyur suspected of involvement in the putsch.
The Turkish authorities issued a warrant for the arrest of a former football player and then a member of Parliament Hakan Shukur and conducted searches in his family's two homes.
Turkish football star of the 1990's - early 2000's attacker Hakan Shukyur is wanted by the authorities in connection with the attempted coup d'état that took place last month.
The forward, who finished his sports career in 2008, is accused of belonging to an "armed terrorist group".
It is about the movement "Hizmet" - a society associated with the famous Turkish religious figure and oppositionist Fethullah Gülen.
It was his president, Erdogan, who was the organizer of the attempted military coup that took place on July 15.
Fethullah Gülen lives in the US, the Turkish authorities demand his extradition.
According to local media, today was issued a warrant for the arrest of Hakan Shukyur, police have already conducted searches in two houses that belong to the family of the former football player.
According to the investigators, in addition to Hakan Shukyur, his father also belonged to the organization of Gülen's Fethullah.
However, neither the former football player nor his relatives were there.
Now he and his family live in the USA.
When he was a football player, Hakan Shukur defended the colors of several Turkish clubs and played for the national team of the country.
He spent most of his career in the Galatasaray.
In the list of foreign clubs are listed Italian "Torino", "Inter" and "Palermo", as well as the English "Blackburn".
True, he did not spend more than one season in either of them.
Hakan Shukyur still remains the most productive striker of the national team of Turkey: he has 112 matches for the national team and 51 goals scored.
In 2013, Hakan Shukur left his post because of the beginning of corruption investigation around the party of Erdogan and his closest associates.
