The Russian Copper Company (RMK) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that RMK undertook the modernization of one of the oldest and environmentally "dirty" enterprises of the country - the Karabash copper smelter.
The Karabash copper smelter was founded by an English joint-stock company led by Leslie Urquhart in 1910.
In Soviet times, it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country's economy, and it actually provided vital activity for the whole city.
However, in the 1990s, due to financial problems, production was stopped, which entailed serious social problems in Karabash.
In 1998, it was decided to resume work of the Karabash copper smelter.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabash plant - the ecological one.
By the beginning of the 2000s Karabash was already notorious as a zone of ecological disaster.
The situation on "Karabashmedi" began to change in 2004, after the enterprise passed under the management of the Russian copper company.
The company began to modernize production, which gradually began to reduce the environmental burden on the environment.
This was recently noted by the Governor of the Chelyabinsk Region, Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in the early days of July.
The head of the South Urals called the changes that have taken place with the company since Karabashmed moved to the RMK group.
The main event for the modernization of Karabashmedi in recent years has been the construction of a new sulfuric acid shop, which allows to capture up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the president of the Russian copper company Vsevolod Levin, the volume of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of "Karabashmed" CJSC is the reconstruction of converter conversion.
Replacement of three converters, dusters, flue duct is planned for the end of 2017.
The project cost is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016 it is planned to launch a new workshop for the purification of industrial effluents worth 1 billion rubles.
In turn, the amount of taxes deducted to the budget of the city of Karabash will also grow.
For the entire period of the Tomino GOK project implementation - from the beginning of construction to the commissioning of the second stage - the federal treasury will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the commissioning of GOK into operation, the receipt of taxes to budgets of all levels may amount to 80.9 billion rubles.
During the year of production in the Varna region, 346.3 million rubles were transferred to budgets of different levels.
And this is for the first year.
"The longer a business successfully operates, the amount of deductions may be greater," added Valery Ulanovsky.
In the RMK clarified that in 2015, tax deductions from the Mikheevsky GOK approached 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of RMK's enterprises in the life and development of their territories is not limited to tax deductions.
The enterprises of the RMK help to repair and maintain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, and landscaping.
In 2016, one of the largest social projects of the Russian Copper Company in Karabash was major repairs, and in fact - almost a complete reconstruction of the kindergarten N9 for 95 pupils.
The building, built in 1960, was in an emergency condition.
Also on the territory of the "RMK Arena" there will be a landscaped park with an artificial pond, underground and overground parking lots for 600 cars, cafes and sports shops.
"RMK Arena" will allow to conduct spectacular professional sports events of international level.
But the main task of this project is to make physical education and sports in comfortable conditions accessible to Chelyabinsk residents, first of all for children.
