WSJ: The US is considering the issue of imposing sanctions against the Russian Federation because of the breaking of the servers of democrats.
US officials are considering the introduction of new sanctions against Russia in response to the hacking of the servers of the Democratic Party, writes The Wall Street Journal, citing sources.
It is reported that for the imposition of sanctions, the US President Barack Obama's administration will have to formally accuse Russia or Russian-backed hackers in attacking the servers.
