FAS fined Google almost half a billion rubles
The reason was the violation of competition in the mobile applications market.
The antimonopoly proceedings were initiated on the initiative of Yandex.
The Russian company claimed that Google provides smartphone manufacturers access to Android components on terms that prohibited the pre-installation of applications from other developers, in particular, from Yandex.
FAS found confirmation of these claims and found that the company abused the dominant position in the market and forced mobile device manufacturers to install other applications together with the Google Play store.
Following the audit, the Federal Antimonopoly Service decided to punish Google, said Deputy Head of the Federal Antimonopoly Service Alexei Dotsenko.
The fine must be paid within 60 days after the entry into force of the order.
The FAS concluded that the law on the protection of competition must be observed by all companies, including transnational corporations.
In turn, Google intends to study the solution first and only then determine with further actions: to execute it or to challenge it.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service recognized the company as a violator of the competition law in September of last year and ordered to adjust the contracts until December 18.
However, Google did not agree to this.
Since then, the company and the department are conducting legal proceedings.
The FAS noted that, despite the fine, they are discussing with Google the possibility of concluding a settlement agreement.
This measure will lead to nothing.
Such an opinion "Echo of Moscow" was expressed by the leading analyst of the Mobile research group Eldar Murtazin.
Murtazin also noted that the penalty will not affect either the users or the competitiveness of the corporation.
