Bulgaria shows inflation for the first time in 8 months
Inflation in Bulgaria was 1% monthly in July, as national statistics show.
This is the highest rate for years (since June 2012) and the first above zero since October last year, when positive 0.2% was shown.
The average annual inflation, measured by the CPI, was -0.8% over the last 12 months (August 2015 - July 2016) compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014 - July 2015).
The consumer price index in July 2016 compared with June 2016 was 101.0%, ie monthly inflation was 1.0%.
The inflation rate from the beginning of the year (July 2016 as compared to December 2015) was -0.2%, and the annual inflation in July 2016 in comparison with July 2015 was -0.2%.
In July 2016, in comparison with the previous month, the increase was observed in the following groups of consumer goods: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7%), transport (1.8%), recreation and culture (6.3%), restaurants and hotels (1.2%), other goods and services (0.3%).
Prices fell on clothes and footwear (2.2%), furniture, household appliances and regular maintenance (0.5%), health (0.1%).
Prices remained at the same level as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco, housing, water, electricity, gas and other fuels, communication systems, and education.
